Putting your key in your bag.

295
00:22:55,050 --> 00:22:58,360
So Beagle with a goldfish memory
like you won’t forget it again.

296
00:23:00,370 --> 00:23:01,610
So I’m not only a dog,

297
00:23:02,000 --> 00:23:03,050
but a fish too?

298
00:23:05,350 --> 00:23:06,340
You’re everything.

299
00:23:11,020 --> 00:23:13,520
This Buddy takes really good care of me.

300
00:23:28,810 --> 00:23:30,260
(Since you started talking about Yotha,)

301
00:23:31,160 --> 00:23:32,340
you haven’t stopped smiling.

302
00:23:33,890 --> 00:23:34,760
Don’t tell us

303
00:23:35,130 --> 00:23:35,940
That you

304
00:23:36,650 --> 00:23:37,810
(Like Yotha!)

305
00:23:49,170 --> 00:23:50,200
I’m thirsty.

306
00:23:51,410 --> 00:23:52,040
For milk.

307
00:23:54,120 --> 00:23:54,700
I want some milk.

308
00:24:10,700 --> 00:24:11,170
Here.

309
00:24:13,270 --> 00:24:13,930
A treat for my buddy.

310
00:24:14,610 --> 00:24:15,080
Hmm?

311
00:24:22,770 --> 00:24:23,500
Let me put the straw in for you.

312
00:24:28,910 --> 00:24:29,410
Drink it.

313
00:24:39,500 --> 00:24:40,070
Is it good?

314
00:24:40,410 --> 00:24:40,900
Mm.

315
00:24:41,630 --> 00:24:43,900
If you want more, feel free to grab more.

316
00:24:44,450 --> 00:24:45,180
I’m happy to share.

317
00:24:50,120 --> 00:24:51,100
But I want you to grab it for me.

318
00:24:55,380 --> 00:24:56,150
Don’t you have hands?

319
00:24:57,930 --> 00:24:58,400
I do.

320
00:25:00,300 --> 00:25:01,240
But I have you too.

321
00:25:11,730 --> 00:25:12,230
I’m done.

322
00:25:14,620 --> 00:25:15,150
I’m sleepy.

323
00:25:17,760 --> 00:25:18,400
Are you going to sleep now?

324
00:25:28,500 --> 00:25:29,500
(Don’t tell us)

325
00:25:29,990 --> 00:25:30,810
(That you)

326
00:25:31,190 --> 00:25:32,360
Like Yotha!

327
00:25:34,780 --> 00:25:35,830
Don’t be delusional, Gun!

328
00:26:01,950 --> 00:26:02,660
Is something wrong?

329
00:26:06,450 --> 00:26:07,380
No, I’m fine.

330
00:26:14,970 --> 00:26:15,770
I said I’m fine.

331
00:26:24,890 --> 00:26:25,510
Yotha.

332
00:26:26,560 --> 00:26:27,140
What?

333
00:26:28,580 --> 00:26:29,450
(So did Yotha.)

334
00:26:30,220 --> 00:26:31,640
He got traumatized when he was a kid too.

335
00:26:32,100 --> 00:26:32,730
Really?

336
00:26:33,370 --> 00:26:34,980
Yotha never told me that.

337
00:26:35,010 --> 00:26:36,180
Something traumatized him

338
00:26:36,870 --> 00:26:38,200
and it made him scared of love.

339
00:26:40,500 --> 00:26:44,650
Newton said you’re scared of love.

340
00:26:46,550 --> 00:26:47,170
Is that true?

341
00:26:50,190 --> 00:26:51,150
Why would you believe a drunk person?

342
00:26:52,060 --> 00:26:53,000
I’m not scared of it.

343
00:26:53,670 --> 00:26:55,890
I just don’t believe in it or have faith in it.

344
00:26:57,380 --> 00:26:59,290
Just like how you never think about
trying to sleep with the lights off

345
00:27:00,700 --> 00:27:03,330
because you’re convinced you’ll have to
sleep with them on for the rest of your life.

346
00:27:04,220 --> 00:27:04,980
It’s the same.

347
00:27:12,230 --> 00:27:16,510
But have you ever thought that

348
00:27:17,360 --> 00:27:19,270
one day someone might
make you believe in it again?

349
00:27:19,280 --> 00:27:19,790
No.

350
00:27:27,700 --> 00:27:28,370
Not at all?

351
00:27:33,420 --> 00:27:34,370
How about we compete?

352
00:27:35,250 --> 00:27:35,800
Compete?

353
00:27:36,370 --> 00:27:36,890
Mm.

354
00:27:37,730 --> 00:27:39,830
Whoever overcomes their fear first wins.

355
00:27:41,060 --> 00:27:41,610
For what?

356
00:27:44,170 --> 00:27:48,140
So you can love

357
00:27:48,710 --> 00:27:50,600
and I can live life more easily,

358
00:27:52,830 --> 00:27:53,640
plus, save electricity.

359
00:27:58,570 --> 00:28:00,530
But why do you want me to love again?

360
00:28:08,220 --> 00:28:09,630
It’s not like that.

361
00:28:10,860 --> 00:28:12,200
You’re scared of love.

362
00:28:13,080 --> 00:28:14,140
I’m scared of the dark.

363
00:28:14,680 --> 00:28:15,860
We both have traumas.

364
00:28:20,460 --> 00:28:21,140
That’s all?

365
00:28:24,060 --> 00:28:24,650
Mm.

366
00:28:35,460 --> 00:28:36,000
Okay.

367
00:28:37,530 --> 00:28:40,260
Why did you move your face close to mine?

368
00:28:40,440 --> 00:28:42,600
But once I can love again,

369
00:28:43,950 --> 00:28:45,700
you must take responsibility for my feelings.

370
00:28:47,770 --> 00:28:48,690
What does that have to do with me?

371
00:28:56,940 --> 00:28:57,490
Deal.

372
00:28:58,590 --> 00:29:03,710
♪ It’s you, only you, who teaches me love ♪

373
00:29:03,980 --> 00:29:09,960
♪ It’s you, only you, who makes me see ♪

374
00:29:10,230 --> 00:29:12,500
♪ What true love is like  ♪

375
00:29:12,940 --> 00:29:17,290
