376
00:29:17,570 --> 00:29:18,100
Hey.

377
00:29:24,930 --> 00:29:25,390
Hey.

378
00:29:26,910 --> 00:29:27,420
Gun.

379
00:29:30,000 --> 00:29:30,490
Hey!

380
00:29:31,690 --> 00:29:32,630
Fai, you startled me.

381
00:29:32,920 --> 00:29:33,410
What is it?

382
00:29:33,480 --> 00:29:35,240
What’s wrong with you, Gun?

383
00:29:37,310 --> 00:29:38,300
You won’t answer any of our questions.

384
00:29:39,570 --> 00:29:40,400
Or maybe…

385
00:29:40,420 --> 00:29:40,900
Hey.

386
00:29:41,140 --> 00:29:42,160
Nothing is going on.

387
00:29:43,220 --> 00:29:45,090
Last night I went back to my room

388
00:29:45,110 --> 00:29:47,150
and Yotha came back…

389
00:29:47,180 --> 00:29:49,090
And we took a shower.

390
00:29:50,640 --> 00:29:51,650
We took separate showers.

391
00:29:51,670 --> 00:29:52,980
Then I fell asleep first.

392
00:29:53,030 --> 00:29:56,620
There was nothing suspicious
between Yotha and me.

393
00:29:56,630 --> 00:29:58,820
Oh.

394
00:29:59,690 --> 00:30:02,200
It’s obvious, Kong.

395
00:30:02,980 --> 00:30:03,920
We don’t need a lie detector

396
00:30:04,720 --> 00:30:06,230
because the lie is already out.

397
00:30:07,450 --> 00:30:08,390
Am I not subtle at all?

398
00:30:08,910 --> 00:30:10,690
What happened last night?

399
00:30:11,690 --> 00:30:13,170
Spill everything.

400
00:30:13,240 --> 00:30:14,150
Spill everything.

401
00:30:20,950 --> 00:30:24,500
I and Yotha…

402
00:30:28,080 --> 00:30:29,164
we’re going to compete.

403
00:30:29,820 --> 00:30:30,402
Compete in what?

404
00:30:32,696 --> 00:30:33,779
I’m scared of the dark.

405
00:30:34,754 --> 00:30:35,896
Yotha is scared of love.

406
00:30:35,936 --> 00:30:39,601
Whoever overcomes their fear first wins.

407
00:30:42,954 --> 00:30:45,600
If you’re not shy, why are your ears red?

408
00:30:48,634 --> 00:30:50,000
There’s more to it than that, right?

409
00:30:53,810 --> 00:30:54,299
No.

410
00:30:59,696 --> 00:31:00,349
Well,

411
00:31:01,644 --> 00:31:02,804
Yotha said

412
00:31:04,782 --> 00:31:09,062
if he can overcome his fear…

413
00:31:09,989 --> 00:31:11,400
Well…

414
00:31:11,700 --> 00:31:12,358
What?

415
00:31:12,382 --> 00:31:12,875
Hmm?

416
00:31:14,250 --> 00:31:16,179
I must take responsibility for his feelings.

417
00:31:17,444 --> 00:31:17,967
What?

418
00:31:19,331 --> 00:31:20,634
Did Yotha really say that?

419
00:31:22,386 --> 00:31:23,398
After he said

420
00:31:23,785 --> 00:31:25,004
you must take responsibility for his feelings,

421
00:31:25,228 --> 00:31:27,539
what did you two do?

422
00:31:35,922 --> 00:31:36,837
Nothing.

423
00:31:37,022 --> 00:31:37,586
We each went to sleep.

424
00:31:41,150 --> 00:31:42,838
- Sadhu, if you’re lying, I hope you…
- Hey, Fai.

425
00:31:43,533 --> 00:31:44,051
Don’t!

426
00:31:44,422 --> 00:31:45,404
My family takes cursing seriously.

427
00:31:45,903 --> 00:31:47,303
My mom won’t even let me swear.

428
00:31:47,340 --> 00:31:48,395
It’s a serious and sensitive matter.

429
00:31:49,299 --> 00:31:50,354
I’ll let you get away with it this time.

430
00:31:53,875 --> 00:31:56,398
Did you give him your word

431
00:31:56,808 --> 00:31:59,263
that you’d take responsibility for his feelings?

432
00:32:00,970 --> 00:32:02,786
I don’t think so.

433
00:32:02,900 --> 00:32:03,767
It’s too late, right?

434
00:32:04,029 --> 00:32:04,497
Yeah.

435
00:32:05,870 --> 00:32:06,634
What do you mean ‘it’s too late’?

436
00:32:07,632 --> 00:32:09,798
You’ve really fallen for Yotha, haven’t you?

437
00:32:12,829 --> 00:32:13,604
Well,

438
00:32:15,663 --> 00:32:16,841
I’m…

439
00:32:17,456 --> 00:32:18,915
not…

440
00:32:19,044 --> 00:32:20,105
You’re not into him?

441
00:32:20,502 --> 00:32:21,653
I’m not sure.

442
00:32:23,853 --> 00:32:24,885
Oh, shit.

443
00:32:25,303 --> 00:32:26,020
Fai,

444
00:32:26,400 --> 00:32:27,401
please don’t tell Yotha.

445
00:32:27,420 --> 00:32:28,090
I beg you.

446
00:32:28,856 --> 00:32:29,420
Of course not.

447
00:32:30,137 --> 00:32:31,075
I won’t tell your secret.

448
00:32:32,007 --> 00:32:34,001
But when will you be sure?

449
00:32:38,214 --> 00:32:38,703
Listen.

450
00:32:39,315 --> 00:32:40,002
I have a shortcut.

451
00:32:42,040 --> 00:32:44,610
TEST YOUR FEELINGS FOR YOUR FRIEND QUIZ
ANSWER YES OR NO

452
00:32:45,848 --> 00:32:47,210
Will it work?

453
00:32:47,434 --> 00:32:48,402
If we don’t try, we’ll never know.

454
00:32:49,779 --> 00:32:51,054
What do you want to do, Gun?

455
00:32:51,413 --> 00:32:52,503
I’m not forcing you.

456
00:32:55,871 --> 00:32:56,601
Are you going to try it?

457
00:33:12,899 --> 00:33:13,494
Ugh.

458
00:33:13,816 --> 00:33:14,622
Damn it.

459
00:33:15,702 --> 00:33:16,740
Why did you touch my hand?

460
00:33:17,430 --> 00:33:18,857
- I’m in a bad mood.
- I’ll go wash my hands.

461
00:33:19,031 --> 00:33:19,668
Go.

462
00:33:21,431 --> 00:33:21,946
Arm.

463
00:33:25,008 --> 00:33:27,007
Can I still switch to another field?

464
00:33:28,500 --> 00:33:30,662
- It’s only the second year but I’m already dying here.
- 10.

465
00:33:30,800 --> 00:33:32,200
- You look dead.
- 9, 8.

466
00:33:32,564 --> 00:33:32,951
7.

467
00:33:33,020 --> 00:33:33,434
6.

468
00:33:33,450 --> 00:33:33,777
5.

469
00:33:33,798 --> 00:33:35,010
4, 3, 2, 1.

470
00:33:35,040 --> 00:33:35,958
Hi, Arc.

471
00:33:35,973 --> 00:33:36,497
I knew it.

472
00:33:36,979 --> 00:33:37,509
Hi.

473
00:33:37,619 --> 00:33:38,800
Where are you going after this?

474
00:33:39,194 --> 00:33:40,321
We’re not going anywhere.

475
00:33:40,634 --> 00:33:42,417
Just walking to the car is tiring enough.

476
00:33:42,691 --> 00:33:43,677
Then let’s split here.

477
00:33:45,357 --> 00:33:47,247
If you don’t get something in your lessons,

478
00:33:47,312 --> 00:33:48,094
you can always ask me.

479
00:33:48,318 --> 00:33:50,794
But now, let’s go grab something delicious to eat.

480
00:33:51,022 --> 00:33:51,496
Come on.

481
00:33:51,555 --> 00:33:51,995
Let’s go.

482
00:33:52,121 --> 00:33:53,202
I’ll help carry your bag.

483
00:33:53,250 --> 00:33:53,902
Thank you.

484
00:33:54,998 --> 00:33:56,002
I’m leaving now. Bye.

485
00:33:56,693 --> 00:33:57,786
What’s wrong with you?

486
00:33:58,848 --> 00:33:59,635
See you.

487
00:33:59,703 --> 00:34:00,475
See you.

488
00:34:00,783 --> 00:34:02,057
Oh, you’re bragging.

489
00:34:03,985 --> 00:34:05,405
I’m jealous of people in relationships.

490
00:34:06,801 --> 00:34:07,838
I want a partner!

491
00:34:08,608 --> 00:34:09,349
Your partner is here.

492
00:34:10,684 --> 00:34:11,437
I’m picking you up.

493
00:34:11,613 --> 00:34:12,222
Okay.

494
00:34:13,022 --> 00:34:14,285
I’m so tired.

495
00:34:14,530 --> 00:34:15,096
Can you take this?

496
00:34:15,111 --> 00:34:15,570
Sure.

497
00:34:16,865 --> 00:34:18,198
Po, I have to go.

498
00:34:19,632 --> 00:34:20,417
See you, Po.

499
00:34:21,577 --> 00:34:22,041
Let’s go.

500
00:34:25,200 --> 00:34:27,870
Is that a trick?

501
00:34:28,788 --> 00:34:29,825
Let me just try it.

502
00:34:32,345 --> 00:34:33,191
I’m so jealous!

503
00:34:33,740 --> 00:34:35,191
I want a partner!

504
00:34:42,285 --> 00:34:43,207
Let’s try again.

505
00:34:43,459 --> 00:34:44,419
I want a partner!

506
00:34:44,482 --> 00:34:45,545
I want a partner!

507
00:34:45,825 --> 00:34:47,131
I want a partner!

508
00:35:09,779 --> 00:35:10,586
I don’t think so.

509
00:35:10,847 --> 00:35:11,717
I probably got the trick wrong.

510
00:35:21,622 --> 00:35:22,179
You like him!

511
00:35:22,709 --> 00:35:23,814
Keep it down!

512
00:35:26,568 --> 00:35:27,056
Gun,

513
00:35:28,503 --> 00:35:29,717
do you really like Yotha?

514
00:35:30,322 --> 00:35:30,822
Keep it down!

515
00:35:30,896 --> 00:35:32,271
You like my brother, Gun?

516
00:35:32,297 --> 00:35:33,035
Keep it down!

517
00:35:33,056 --> 00:35:33,721
Are you crazy?

518
00:35:33,742 --> 00:35:34,188
Gun!

519
00:35:34,869 --> 00:35:35,368
Beagle.

520
00:35:38,457 --> 00:35:39,160
You like me?

521
00:36:10,671 --> 00:36:12,496
Yotha, listen to me.

522
00:36:13,088 --> 00:36:14,797
It’s not what you think.

523
00:36:15,165 --> 00:36:16,014
You’re getting it wrong

524
00:36:40,770 --> 00:36:41,702
Why did you stop?

525
00:36:44,270 --> 00:36:45,274
You like me, Beagle?

526
00:36:46,971 --> 00:36:47,797
Let go of me.

527
00:36:48,983 --> 00:36:49,471
Let go.

528
00:36:53,954 --> 00:36:55,379
It’s not what you think.

529
00:36:55,471 --> 00:36:56,564
I can explain.

530
00:36:56,580 --> 00:36:57,411
If it’s not what I think,

531
00:36:58,379 --> 00:36:59,699
does that mean you don’t like me?

532
00:37:02,150 --> 00:37:03,106
It’s not that, either.

533
00:37:03,454 --> 00:37:04,106
So it means you like me.

534
00:37:04,394 --> 00:37:06,345
Don’t pressure me now.

535
00:37:06,545 --> 00:37:07,413
I’m slow.

536
00:37:08,020 --> 00:37:09,402
Let me process it first.

537
00:37:14,610 --> 00:37:15,197
Well,

538
00:37:17,022 --> 00:37:21,237
Kong thinks we’re…

539
00:37:22,903 --> 00:37:23,463
Mm-hmm?

540
00:37:24,071 --> 00:37:25,300
In a situationship.

541
00:37:27,389 --> 00:37:28,604
But I already denied it.

542
00:37:31,460 --> 00:37:32,068
And then?

543
00:37:33,625 --> 00:37:37,251
And then he didn’t believe me.

544
00:37:37,850 --> 00:37:40,527
So he made me take this crazy quiz.

545
00:37:40,640 --> 00:37:41,705
I went along with it,

546
00:37:43,167 --> 00:37:44,798
and the result was

547
00:37:48,611 --> 00:37:49,711
I like you.

548
00:37:52,401 --> 00:37:54,902
But there are many different kinds
of "like" and "love."

549
00:37:55,545 --> 00:37:56,241
Right, Yotha?

550
00:37:56,560 --> 00:37:58,413
I might like you as a friend.

551
00:37:58,610 --> 00:37:59,400
What did the quiz say?

552
00:38:01,220 --> 00:38:02,515
Just ignore it.

553
00:38:02,792 --> 00:38:03,502
Question 1?

554
00:38:14,440 --> 00:38:16,397
IN CASE YOU WANT TO TAKE IT
WHEN YOU’RE MORE LEVEL-HEADED

555
00:38:16,397 --> 00:38:18,170
P.S. YOU CAN ASK YOTHA TO TAKE IT TOO.

556
00:38:22,977 --> 00:38:23,897
Do you really want to know?

557
00:38:24,125 --> 00:38:24,897
Do I look like I’m joking?

558
00:38:28,976 --> 00:38:30,897
Just answer yes or no.

559
00:38:32,665 --> 00:38:33,294
Question 1.

560
00:38:34,121 --> 00:38:35,558
You feel an instant connection.

561
00:38:40,065 --> 00:38:40,598
Yes.

562
00:38:45,311 --> 00:38:46,010
Question 2.

563
00:38:47,765 --> 00:38:49,951
You think of them all the time.

564
00:38:50,346 --> 00:38:50,899
No.

565
00:38:54,631 --> 00:38:55,402
Question 3.

566
00:38:56,720 --> 00:38:58,250
You steal a glance at them
every time you get a chance.

567
00:39:04,078 --> 00:39:04,625
Yes.

568
00:39:05,149 --> 00:39:05,638
Really?

569
00:39:08,041 --> 00:39:09,902
Why do you steal a glance?

570
00:39:12,828 --> 00:39:13,854
I like looking at that dog.

571
00:39:14,527 --> 00:39:15,327
It’s cute.

572
00:39:16,677 --> 00:39:17,268
You jerk.

573
00:39:18,379 --> 00:39:18,922
Question 4.

574
00:39:19,731 --> 00:39:21,579
You’re in a better mood than usual
when you’re near them.

575
00:39:23,367 --> 00:39:24,026
